Falun Dafa practitioners in Hualien City on Taiwan's East Coast held activities on Sunday, February 16, 2020, to raise awareness of the persecution in China and collect signatures for a petition to help end the atrocities.

They held their activities outside the Hualien Train Station, which is the main entry point for visitors to Hualien County. About 30 practitioners demonstrated the Falun Gong exercises along the roadside, and a group of practitioners later performed a traditional Chinese waist drum dance.

A couple who had recently immigrated from the United States to live in Taiwan stopped to take photos of the practitioners’ activities. The wife told practitioners she had often seen large-scale parades held by Falun Dafa practitioners in the U.S. She said she was happy to also see practitioners in Hualien City.

snippet.textDisplay: Lifelong United fan here. Our football is a joke, pathetic, cowardly, humorous, pedestrian, unimaginative and Ole relies on individual talent to scrape through games. Not just an ordinary manager, he's a bottom tier manager. Besides Norwegian ones, which clubs would realistically hire him as their manager? Honestly. A year gone and after 200 million spent we play football that is hard to watch. I wanted Poch from the start, and was disillusioned when the majority of fans swept Ole into a job he just wasn't good enough for. We need a manager that says "my way or the highway" and has the force of character to mold the squad as they see fit for us to be able to enjoy watching United again. I couldn't care less if we lose games and don't win trophies, the football needs to played the right way. Attack attack attack! Remember that?!
